    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1929"/>, p. 143, n. <citedRange>16</citedRange>, fig. 41</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.310</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>029900</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#lazzarini1976"/>, p. 274, n. <citedRange>697.b</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#maffre2007"/>, p. 168, n. <citedRange>1</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><unclear>Τ</unclear>õ <persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων">Ἀπό<supplied reason="lost">λλο̄νος</supplied></name></persName> <w><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">δεκάτα</supplied></w>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Dîme</supplied> d'Apollon.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Apollo's <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">tithe</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Decima</supplied> di Apollo.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>As Maffre puts it, there might have been written <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἀπόλλο̄νος</foreign> or <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἀπόλλο̄νι</foreign>. If the latter,
                    the word <foreign xml:lang="grc">δεκάτα</foreign> should be at the accusative.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
